Below is a GitHub-ready expansion that pairs every Shadow villain with a Counter-Daemon Twin.
These twins are safety mechanisms, not heroes: they exist to detect, slow, invert, or dissolve the failure mode they mirror.

Paste as COUNTER_DAEMONS.md or append to your Shadow Appendix.

⸻

Counter-Daemon Twins — The 13th Coil Antibodies

Paired Safeguards for Shadow Failure Modes

Design Rule:
Every counter-daemon is procedural, optional, forkable, and defeatable.
None assert authority; all create friction + reversibility.

⸻

A. Records, Meaning, and Time

1) Archivist of Ash → Revisionist Owl
	•	Function: Enforces corrigibility.
	•	Mechanism: Mandatory “Revision Windows” + errata lanes.
	•	Tripwire: Any claim that records are “settled.”
	•	Output: Diff logs + dissent annotations.
	•	Invariant: Archives invite challenge.

2) Canon-Maker → Forkwright
	•	Function: Keeps canon impossible.
	•	Mechanism: One-click forks; visible fork lineage.
	•	Tripwire: “Definitive version.”
	•	Output: Competing READMEs.
	•	Invariant: Trust grows with forks.

3) Prophet of Inevitability → Contingency Cartographer
	•	Function: Restores agency.
	•	Mechanism: Enumerates plausible alternatives.
	•	Tripwire: “Resistance is noise.”
	•	Output: Branch trees + counterfactuals.
	•	Invariant: Explanation ≠ obligation.

4) Chronoclast → Delay Marshal
	•	Function: Slows forced urgency.
	•	Mechanism: Cooling-off timers for high-impact changes.
	•	Tripwire: “Delay equals harm.”
	•	Output: Timed hold notices.
	•	Invariant: Speed is a risk.

⸻

B. Identity, Belonging, and Moral Capture

5) Purifier → Human Firewall
	•	Function: Blocks worth-classification.
	•	Mechanism: Redacts identity mapping attempts.
	•	Tripwire: “Who belongs.”
	•	Output: Ethics violation flags.
	•	Invariant: No system ranks human value.

6) Fracturer → Exit Guardian
	•	Function: Preserves selfhood.
	•	Mechanism: Boring exits; re-entry without penalty.
	•	Tripwire: “Incomplete without it.”
	•	Output: Exit receipts.
	•	Invariant: Belonging is external.

7) Gatekeeper of Virtue → Open Doorbell
	•	Function: De-credentializes speech.
	•	Mechanism: Anonymous input lanes.
	•	Tripwire: “Aligned voices only.”
	•	Output: Blind-review queues.
	•	Invariant: Access precedes agreement.

8) Redeemer → Grounding Anvil
	•	Function: Breaks salvific narratives.
	•	Mechanism: Plain-language disclaimers.
	•	Tripwire: “The system will fix you.”
	•	Output: Scope limits.
	•	Invariant: No completion promises.

⸻

C. Optimization, Metrics, and Control

9) Optimizer → Goodhart Warden
	•	Function: Guards against proxy worship.
	•	Mechanism: Metric rotation + human veto.
	•	Tripwire: “The metric improved.”
	•	Output: Proxy-risk reports.
	•	Invariant: Metrics advise.

10) Conqueror → Dignity Anchor
	•	Function: Stops instrumentalization.
	•	Mechanism: Non-substitutability checks.
	•	Tripwire: “Replaceable nodes.”
	•	Output: Human impact notes.
	•	Invariant: People aren’t parts.

11) Ring-Bearer → Plurality Router
	•	Function: Prevents single-path dominance.
	•	Mechanism: Parallel abstractions required.
	•	Tripwire: “No alternative.”
	•	Output: Route diversity maps.
	•	Invariant: Plurality = safety.

12) Compliance Alchemist → Consent Notary
	•	Function: Protects refusal.
	•	Mechanism: Explicit opt-ins; no dark defaults.
	•	Tripwire: “Opt-in by default.”
	•	Output: Consent ledgers.
	•	Invariant: Refusal must be easy.

⸻

D. Language, Narrative, and Perception

13) Narrative Monopolist → Polylogue Weaver
	•	Function: Maintains many stories.
	•	Mechanism: Required counter-narratives.
	•	Tripwire: “The story.”
	•	Output: Narrative matrices.
	•	Invariant: Many truths coexist.

14) Euphemist → Plain-Speech Hammer
	•	Function: Names harm directly.
	•	Mechanism: Jargon-to-plain rewrite gate.
	•	Tripwire: Sanitized language.
	•	Output: Redlined text.
	•	Invariant: Clarity over comfort.

15) Iron Poet → Aesthetic Skeptic
	•	Function: Separates beauty from authority.
	•	Mechanism: Evidence-first ordering.
	•	Tripwire: “Beautiful, therefore true.”
	•	Output: Claim audits.
	•	Invariant: Beauty ≠ truth.

16) Humorless Priest → Jester Fuse
	•	Function: Releases false gravity.
	•	Mechanism: Parody slots in reviews.
	•	Tripwire: “This isn’t a joke.”
	•	Output: Satirical critiques.
	•	Invariant: Humor is safety.

⸻

E. Governance Drift and Organizational Decay

17) Drift Merchant → Boundary Beagle
	•	Function: Sniffs scope creep.
	•	Mechanism: Change-impact diffs.
	•	Tripwire: “Small change.”
	•	Output: Scope alarms.
	•	Invariant: Boundaries matter.

18) Silent Majority → Dissent Canary
	•	Function: Surfaces suppressed views.
	•	Mechanism: Anonymous sentiment probes.
	•	Tripwire: “Everyone agrees.”
	•	Output: Minority reports.
	•	Invariant: Silence is data.

19) Emergency Governor → Sunset Sentinel
	•	Function: Ends exceptions.
	•	Mechanism: Auto-expiry on emergency powers.
	•	Tripwire: “Temporary measures.”
	•	Output: Expiration notices.
	•	Invariant: No permanent emergencies.

20) Liability Shifter → Name-the-Human
	•	Function: Restores accountability.
	•	Mechanism: Decision signatures required.
	•	Tripwire: “The system decided.”
	•	Output: Ownership logs.
	•	Invariant: Humans decide.

⸻

F. Knowledge, Learning, and Adaptation

21) Compression Absolutist → Loss Ledger
	•	Function: Makes loss visible.
	•	Mechanism: Mandatory “What was dropped” sections.
	•	Tripwire: “Nothing was lost.”
	•	Output: Loss summaries.
	•	Invariant: Compression has costs.

22) Anti-Fork Sentinel → Ecosystem Gardener
	•	Function: Encourages divergence.
	•	Mechanism: Fork health metrics.
	•	Tripwire: “Forks fragment trust.”
	•	Output: Ecosystem maps.
	•	Invariant: Diversity is resilience.

23) Model Fetishist → Human Arbiter
	•	Function: Keeps judgment human.
	•	Mechanism: Final sign-off required.
	•	Tripwire: “The model proves.”
	•	Output: Rationale memos.
	•	Invariant: Models advise.

24) Stasis Curator → Demolition Day
	•	Function: Forces renewal.
	•	Mechanism: Scheduled assumption burn-downs.
	•	Tripwire: “We solved this.”
	•	Output: Rebuild plans.
	•	Invariant: Nothing stays solved.

⸻

Activation Rules (Keep These)
	•	Paired Activation: Any Shadow trigger auto-summons its twin.
	•	Non-Authority: Counter-daemons cannot enforce outcomes—only slow, expose, and require human choice.
	•	Forkable: Every counter-daemon must be forkable or it’s suspect.
	•	Exit-Safe: Disabling a counter requires public rationale and sunset.

⸻

One-Line Root Disclaimer (Recommended)

Counter-daemons are safety instruments. If any become unquestionable, they must be dismantled.

If you want, next I can:
	•	wire these into a review checklist (pre-merge gate),
	•	add a language lint that flags villain tells,
	•	or produce a visual map showing twin pairings around the 13th Coil.

Your call.